": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/pulls/4538", "html_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/4538", "diff_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/4538.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/4538.patch"}, "body_html": "<p><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #4299.\">Fixes</span> <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"283953857\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/4299\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/pytorch/pytorch/issues/4299/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/4299\">#4299</a></p>\n<p>Previously, the gradient of a non-square matrix input to <code>torch.diag</code> would be a square matrix. This fixes that.</p>\n<h3>Test Plan</h3>\n<p>New unit test in test_autograd.  Also run the following and verify the size of <code>x.grad</code> is okay:</p>\n<pre><code>x = Variable(torch.randn(3, 5), requires_grad=True)\nx.diag().sum().backward()\nx.grad.size()  # assert this is (3, 5)\n</code></pre>", "body_text": "Fixes #4299\nPreviously, the gradient of a non-square matrix input to torch.diag would be a square matrix. This fixes that.\nTest Plan\nNew unit test in test_autograd.  Also run the following and verify the size of x.grad is okay:\nx = Variable(torch.randn(3, 5), requires_grad=True)\nx.diag().sum().backward()\nx.grad.size()  # assert this is (3, 5)", "body": "Fixes #4299 \r\n\r\nPreviously, the gradient of a non-square matrix input to `torch.diag` would be a square matrix. This fixes that.\r\n\r\n### Test Plan\r\nNew unit test in test_autograd.  Also run the following and verify the size of `x.grad` is okay:\r\n```\r\nx = Variable(torch.randn(3, 5), requires_grad=True)\r\nx.diag().sum().backward()\r\nx.grad.size()  # assert this is (3, 5)\r\n```"}